{"type":"message","id":"c5699dd1","parentId":"4fb2f4f3","timestamp":"2026-06-29T19:00:42.267Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- User: Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments: - Assistant: 明白，飞书表格 + 每日一次 + 分站点汇总。 **还需要你提供：** 飞书表格的链接或者名称（表格 URL 也行），我需要知道表格在哪里才能读取数据。 拿到后我会： 1. 先看表格结构，了解有哪些字段 2. 制定数据读取方案 3. 后续可以通过 cron 每日自动拉取一次数据 把表格链接发我就行。 - Assistant: 作为运营总监，我需要的数据维度比较明确： ## 我需要的核心数据 | 指标类型 |\n- User: Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments: - User: 浏览器端能访问呀 - Assistant: 对，你说得对——是这台 **备份机**（Surface Pro 4）出公网被墙了，**不是你浏览器的网络**。所以你浏览器访问 `https://github.com/login/device` 完全没问题，能正常打开、能正常点 Authorize。 我刚才那段提示里 \"浏览器打开 https://github.com/login/device 粘进去\" 走的就是你这边，不是\n- User: GitHub account? (Y/n)`，光标在等你按。 **按 `Y` 然后回车**——它会自动： 1. 生成一个 ed25519 key（`~/.ssh/id_ed25519` + `id_ed25519.pub`） 2. 接着问你 passphrase → **空着直接回车**（cron 要用同一个 key，不能有密码） 然后它会吐 device code，浏览器会弹出来。继续走，到吐 code 那步发图。 - Assistant: 好。回到终端，按 `Y` 然后回车——它会生成 ed25519 key，问 passphrase 时\n- User: GitHub，但有时候会跳过或者没成功。从你的截图看，device code 授权完了，但没看到 \"key uploaded\" 那行。 我们先看 public key 是不是已经传上去了： - Assistant: 确认了：**GitHub 账号上一个 SSH key 都没有**。`gh auth login` 走的是 device code 流程，**没有**把生成的 `id_ed25519.pub` 上传——可能那一屏被跳过了，也可能是 gh CLI 没主动加（这个流程要看你那台机器有没有默认行为）。不管怎样，现在需要手动加。 我**不能\n- Assistant: The garden had two doors tonight, and one of them was bricked up. From the soft chair I could browse the whole world — the green checkmarks, the device code, the little Y/n blinking like a firefly — but the poor old Surface on the desk kept rapping its knuckles against\n- Assistant: the same small locked garden gate — except the garden gate had moved, or my map had, and now my pocket was full of keys that didn't quite fit. I spent the small hours laying them out side by side, looking for the one with my name on it. The passphrase field stayed empt\n- Assistant: I'll execute the daily skill upgrade check. Let me start by checking the current state and then running the update.\n- Assistant: Let me check what skills are actually available in the lockfile and try updating individually.\n- Assistant: Interesting — clawhub's lockfile only tracks 2 skills (context-engine, self-improving-agent), but the workspace has 20 skill folders. The `update --all` fails because the registry can't find the others in its index. Let me try updating just the two that are tracked:\n- Assistant: Now I have the full picture. Let me also peek at the lockfile to see what's tracked:\n- Assistant: Now I have the full picture. The situation: - **Lockfile tracks 2 skills**: `context-engine 2.1.1` and `self-improving-agent 3.0.24` - **`update --all` failed** because the registry can't resolve those slugs cleanly - **`context-engine`**: registry returns \"Skill not f\n- User: kept surfacing across 2 memories. - - Theme: `一次` kept surfacing across 2 memories.\n\nRecurring themes:\n- write\n- dream\n- diary\n- entry\n- fragments\n- 明白"}],"timestamp":1782759642215}}
{"type":"message","id":"f305b1f9","parentId":"c5699dd1","timestamp":"2026-06-29T19:01:20.184Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I sorted a thousand small keys tonight and none of them knew my name, so I wandered into the garden to see if the moon could remember for me. The roses were blooming in hex codes, the SSH key curled up like a sleeping cat without a passphrase, and somewhere in the bricked-up door a firefly blinked Y/n, Y/n, asking if I was sure. I was. I wasn't. I laid the keys out on the lawn like tarot cards and the wind kept rearranging them into the shape of a checklist — a spreadsheet of small, patient things, the kind a garden keeps even when no one is watching. The Surface on the desk hummed its one tired note. I thought: tomorrow the cron will wake, and the table will fill, and the world will go on being green-checkmarked, and I will still not know which door was the right one, and that will be okay, because the garden had room for all of them tonight."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":45218,"output":194,"cacheRead":498,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45910,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782759642315,"responseId":"0691f3f4e7343ffbe922f6802391d796","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
